To avoid the problem of the raw eggs you can cook them. Whisk the egg yolks with the sugar in a metal bowl, put it over a saucepan of simmering water, whisk it constantly until the candy thermometer registers 165' and mixture thickens, about 4 minutes, let cool completely, whisk occasionally. For the egg whites, substitute them with 1 cup of whipped cream, and follow the recipe as it says. The taste is as good as it is or even better than when the eggs are raw. Try it you won't regret it.

