Rating: 0
Instead of a sabayon, where you may or may not reach a safe cooking temp before you curdle your custard, you can also make a pate a bombe using the yolks and sugar - just cook the sugar in a pot to softball stage and pour down the side of the mixing bowl onto your yolks while the mixer is whipping away. Just like making Italian meringue, but with yolks instead, and you are sure that your food is safe. The pate a bombe is also stiffer, and will help with consistency issues. Another way to get your tiramisu to set is to add a little gelatin.

