I liked the flavor and texture of the mascarpone mixture. The amount of coffee and directions for dipping the lady fingers, however, resulted in far too soggy cookies. I dipped only one cookie for the prescribed four seconds on each side, and it disintegrated. I rolled the others quickly in the coffee liquid but the finished tiramisu had a pool of coffee in the bottom of the pan, and the cookies had lost all of their body. The lady fingers I bought were imported from Italy, but I imagine they aren't the same as true Italian lady fingers, which I hear are larger and more dense than what we find in the US. Most people making this recipe will likely find the kind of ladyfingers I did, so I would suggest cutting the coffee way down (two cups seems absurd) and drizzling some coffee over the cookies rather than dunking them in the liquid. I'd also add some Marsala to the mascarpone mixture if I make this recipe again.

