I'm currently living in Italy and I made this for a dinner party - the Italians raved! One woman said it was as good as her mom's - apparently very high praise, and others said it was the best they've had. The only changes I made to the recipe were based on prior reviews. I used only 1/2 cup of sugar, a bit more mascarpone (250 g), 1 cup of espresso, and chocolate shavings in between layers as well as on top. It took a total of 24 savoiardi to fill my dish, I only dipped the cookies for 2-3 seconds per side, and beat the whipping cream to firm peaks. This is going in my permanent file.

