Wonderful! Nice basic tiramisu. For the coffee, it's nice with a bit of cream mixed in, and brandy, rum and a teeny bit of sambuca in it. (You can't taste the licorice at all, but somehow the sambuca makes it fab!) I also cook the egg yolks: use a small bowl set over hot (not boiling) water. Whisk the eggs continuously until they're pale lemon-coloured. This doesn't change the texture at all (as long as you stir it constantly) and voila! goodbye salmonella risk.

