I made a few changes, based on researching a few recipes and my experience with tiramisu. First, only dip the cookies for 1 second per side - just put them in, flip them, and remove. You only need one cup of coffee. Second, I needed 24 large cookies for the 8" square dish I used. Third, I skipped the whipped cream, because it looked filling enough, and it was still great. Fourth, I put grated chocolate in both layers of filling. These are just personal choices, but the dish came out really great. My husband took some to the office to have his friends taste it!

